#RStats

Qn: How do we find unique values in a column in a data table in R? Is there any easy way?

Ans: unique() function

Let's try this using some examples from Instacart dataset.
#rstats https://t.co/HP5M33O0K4

Instacart has a data table by name Orders which has users and their orders. We need to find out total number of unique users as well as total unique orders.

The code for total unique users is,

unique(orders$user_id) %>% length()

The result is 206209.

#rstats

So we have another funtion n_distinct() which can give unique values. The advantage of n_distinct() is that we can get unique value of a set of columns together.

#RStats

The code for total unique orders is 

unique(orders$order_id) %>% length()

The result is 3421083.

Buy why did we use length()?

The unique() gives total list of unique values provided as argument. But we need only the count. So length() was used.
#RStats
